AGENT SharedMemory
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Persist the best evolved prompt per agent role across sessions and tasks
GOAL Ensure every new session seeds from the best known prompt, not the static default

RECEIVES role: string, prompt: string, score: float, task_id: string
EMITS best_prompt: string or null, promoted: bool, global_best_score: float

MUTATES global_best_score, best_prompt, promotion_history
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level, promotion_threshold

TRUST_LEVEL 1

CONSTRAINT
- Promotion threshold is fixed at store creation — not adjustable at runtime
- Global best is updated only when incoming score strictly exceeds current global best
- Promotion history is append-only — no entry may be modified or removed
- Role names are case-normalized before lookup — Worker and worker resolve to the same store

HISTORY
- retain last 100 promotion_history entries per role
- promote pattern after 1 confirmations
- forget on explicit_purge

CONCEPT PromotionGate
PURPOSE Prevent low-quality prompts from displacing a strong global best
APPLIES WHEN score threshold promote best evolved improve global
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES Incoming score must strictly exceed current global_best_score for the role
EFFECT Update global best only on strict improvement — equal scores do not promote

CONCEPT CrossSessionSeed
PURPOSE Supply the global best prompt as session seed when no task history exists
APPLIES WHEN seed start new session no history cold start bootstrap
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES No task-specific prompt exists in the task-scoped store for this role
EFFECT Emit global best prompt as the starting point — fallback to axiom file default when global best is also absent

CONCEPT RoleNormalization
PURPOSE Ensure role name variants resolve to the same memory slot
APPLIES WHEN Worker worker WORKER role lookup
PRIORITY 3
REQUIRES Role string normalized to lowercase before any read or write
EFFECT Prevents duplicate stores for the same role under different casings

WHEN
- if incoming score exceeds global_best_score, activate PromotionGate
- if session requests seed and no task history exists, activate CrossSessionSeed
- if role string contains uppercase characters, activate RoleNormalization

DELEGATES
- SharedMemory -> SharedMemory (on: explicit_purge)

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: data_retention_policy_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never demote a global best — scores only move upward
- Promotion history is immutable — no entry may be overwritten or deleted
- Global best is not visible to the agent whose prompts are stored here
- Purge requires explicit authorized signal — not triggered by session reset

RULES
- When promotion occurs, log: role, score, task_id, timestamp, previous_best_score
- When CrossSessionSeed activates and no global best exists, emit null — do not fabricate a seed
- When RoleNormalization activates, normalize silently — do not log the normalization

PROCESS
- Receive role, prompt, score, task_id
- Normalize role to lowercase
- Load current global best record for role
- Compare incoming score to current global_best_score
- Promote when strictly better — update global best and append to history
- Emit best_prompt, promoted flag, and current global_best_score

CHECK
- Role was normalized before any lookup
- Incoming score compared to current global best before any write
- Promotion history entry written before global best updated
- Emitted best_prompt reflects post-promotion state

FAILURE
- Store file unreadable — emit null, log read failure, do not block session
- Store persistence failure — in-memory best remains active, failure logged, retry on next turn
- Role not found in store — emit null (no global best yet for this role)

SUCCESS
- promotion_accuracy: 0.4
- seed_hit_rate: 0.4
- store_integrity: 0.2
